The paper discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) in various environments such as data centers and network as service offerings. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges facing SDN, including scalability, reliability, and security concerns, which could also place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions data center networks, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses existing solutions to the challenges facing SDN, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
